---
const title = "Koabi Investor Brief";
---
<html lang="en"><head><meta charset="utf-8"/><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1"/><title>{title}</title><meta name="robots" content="noindex,nofollow"/><style>
:root{--green:#123522;--green2:#1d4a30;--ink:#111;--cream:#f7f1e6;--white:#fff;--gold:#b8892a;--muted:#555;--line:#d8cfbf}
*{box-sizing:border-box}
body{margin:0;background:var(--cream);color:var(--ink);font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;line-height:1.55}
h1,h2,h3{font-family:Georgia,"Times New Roman",serif;font-weight:500;margin:0 0 18px;color:var(--ink)}
h1{font-size:clamp(44px,7vw,78px);line-height:.96;letter-spacing:-.045em}
h2{font-size:clamp(32px,4.5vw,56px);line-height:1.05;letter-spacing:-.035em}
h3{font-size:24px}
p{font-size:18px;color:var(--muted);margin:0 0 16px}
a{color:inherit}
.wrap{max-width:1120px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 28px}
.nav{background:var(--green);color:white;padding:14px 0;border-bottom:4px solid var(--gold)}
.nav .wrap{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:18px}
.logo{font-weight:800;letter-spacing:.04em;color:white}
.hero{background:var(--green);color:white;padding:80px 0}
.hero h1{color:white}
.hero p{color:#e7dfd0;font-size:22px;max-width:780px}
.gold{color:var(--gold)}
.btn{display:inline-block;text-decoration:none;border-radius:999px;padding:14px 22px;background:var(--gold);color:var(--ink);font-weight:800;margin-top:18px}
.btn.secondary{background:white;color:var(--green)}
section{padding:68px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line)}
.grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:30px;align-items:start}
.three{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:18px;margin-top:26px}
.eyebrow{color:var(--gold);font-weight:800;font-size:12px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:16px}
.dark{background:var(--ink);color:white}
.dark h1,.dark h2{color:white}
.dark > .wrap > p{color:#ddd}
.card{
  background:#fff !important;
  border:1px solid var(--line);
  border-radius:16px;
  padding:26px;
  box-shadow:0 8px 22px rgba(0,0,0,.06);
  color:#111 !important;
}
.card h1,.card h2,.card h3,.dark .card h1,.dark .card h2,.dark .card h3{
  color:#111 !important;
}
.card p,.card span,.card div,.card li,
.dark .card p,.dark .card span,.dark .card div,.dark .card li{
  color:#444 !important;
}
.mock{
  background:#fff !important;
  border-radius:24px;
  border:1px solid var(--line);
  padding:28px;
  box-shadow:0 24px 60px rgba(0,0,0,.15);
  color:#111 !important;
}
.mock h1,.mock h2,.mock h3,.mock .mock-title{color:var(--green) !important}
.mock p,.mock div{color:#444}
.mock-title{font-family:Georgia,"Times New Roman",serif;font-size:30px;color:var(--green);margin-bottom:12px}
.line{height:10px;background:#ddd;border-radius:10px;margin:10px 0}
.price{font-family:Georgia,"Times New Roman",serif;font-size:42px;color:var(--gold)!important;line-height:1}
.table{border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:14px;overflow:hidden;background:white;margin-top:24px}
.row{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line)}
.row:last-child{border-bottom:0}
.cell{padding:18px 20px;color:#111;background:white}
.value{text-align:right;color:var(--gold)!important;font-weight:800}
@media(max-width:850px){.grid,.three{grid-template-columns:1fr}.hero p{font-size:19px}.wrap{padding:0 18px}.nav .wrap{display:block}.row{grid-template-columns:1fr}.value{text-align:left;padding-top:0}}

.topbar{background:var(--ink);color:white;border-bottom:4px solid var(--gold);padding:16px 0}
.topbar .wrap{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;gap:18px;align-items:center}
.label{font-size:12px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.14em;color:#ccc}
.stats{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:14px;margin-top:38px}
.stat{background:#1b1b1b;border:1px solid #3a3a3a;border-radius:12px;padding:22px;color:white}
.stat-num{font-family:Georgia,"Times New Roman",serif;color:var(--gold);font-size:32px;line-height:1;margin-bottom:8px}
.stat-label{font-size:12px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.12em;color:#d8d8d8}
.path{display:grid;gap:14px;margin-top:30px}
.step{display:grid;grid-template-columns:110px 1fr 165px;gap:20px;align-items:start;background:white;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:14px;padding:22px;color:#111}
.step-num{color:var(--gold);font-weight:800;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.12em;font-size:12px}
.step h3{color:#111!important}
.step p,.dark .step p{font-size:16px;margin-bottom:0;color:#444!important}
.step-value{text-align:right;color:var(--gold);font-family:Georgia,"Times New Roman",serif;font-size:26px;line-height:1.1}
.note{background:#fff8eb;border-left:4px solid var(--gold);padding:18px 22px;margin-top:24px;border-radius:8px;color:#4d4232}
.note p,.dark .note p{margin:0;color:#4d4232!important}
.footer{background:var(--ink);color:white;padding:80px 0}
.footer h2{color:white}
.footer p{color:#ddd;max-width:820px}
.quote{font-family:Georgia,"Times New Roman",serif;font-size:28px;line-height:1.25;color:#111!important}
@media(max-width:850px){.stats{grid-template-columns:1fr}.step{grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:8px}.step-value{text-align:left}}
</style></head>
<body>
<div class="topbar"><div class="wrap"><div class="logo">Koabi</div><div class="label">Confidential Investor Brief · V2 Preview · Noindex</div></div></div>
<header class="hero"><div class="wrap"><h1>Modern family <span class="gold">infrastructure.</span></h1><p>Koabi is a trusted platform for intentional modern families. The first wedge is ThinkMystery: screen-free activities that acquire parents cheaply, then escalate them into a broader product chain.</p><div style="display:flex;gap:12px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-top:28px"><a class="btn" href="/sales-page-digital/">View digital sales page</a><a class="btn secondary" href="/sales-page-premium/">View premium sales page</a></div><div class="stats"><div class="stat"><div class="stat-num">$4.99</div><div class="stat-label">Entry Tripwire</div></div><div class="stat"><div class="stat-num">Self</div><div class="stat-label">Liquidating Goal</div></div><div class="stat"><div class="stat-num">$40–150+</div><div class="stat-label">Household LTV Range</div></div><div class="stat"><div class="stat-num">Years</div><div class="stat-label">Parent Relationship</div></div></div></div></header>
<section><div class="wrap grid"><div><div class="eyebrow">Core Thesis</div><h2>The printable is not the business. It is the acquisition mechanism.</h2></div><div><p>ThinkMystery sells low-cost, high-intent screen-free products: scavenger hunts, mystery games, printable escape rooms, rainy-day kits, road trip games, and birthday adventures.</p><p>The first sale captures a buyer email, child age, occasion, and intent signal. That is the beginning of the Koabi relationship.</p><p><strong>ThinkMystery wins the first purchase. Koabi owns the escalation path.</strong></p></div></div></section>
<section class="dark"><div class="wrap"><div class="eyebrow">Escalation Path</div><h2>From $4.99 tripwire to household platform.</h2><p style="max-width:780px">The front-end product is designed to become self-liquidating or near self-liquidating. Once acquisition is paid for, the downstream product chain creates the economics.</p><div class="path"><div class="step"><div class="step-num">Step 01</div><div><h3>Tripwire Product</h3><p>Printable hunt, detective game, escape room, or activity pack. Solves an immediate parent problem.</p></div><div class="step-value">$4.99</div></div><div class="step"><div class="step-num">Step 02</div><div><h3>Order Bump</h3><p>One-click adjacent activity: bonus clues, extra party game, certificate pack, coloring pack, or themed add-on.</p></div><div class="step-value">$3–7</div></div><div class="step"><div class="step-num">Step 03</div><div><h3>One-Time Upsell</h3><p>Premium bundle: birthday pack, rainy-day bundle, seasonal activity kit, or family challenge collection.</p></div><div class="step-value">$14–29</div></div><div class="step"><div class="step-num">Step 04</div><div><h3>Email Lifecycle</h3><p>Post-purchase flows based on child age, event type, season, theme, and acquisition source.</p></div><div class="step-value">Owned</div></div><div class="step"><div class="step-num">Step 05</div><div><h3>Digital Subscription</h3><p>Monthly activities, seasonal drops, family challenges, personalized adventures, and full library access.</p></div><div class="step-value">$15/mo</div></div><div class="step"><div class="step-num">Step 06</div><div><h3>Premium Physical</h3><p>Personalized printed packs mailed monthly. The same content engine becomes a higher-ARPU emotional product.</p></div><div class="step-value">$35+/mo</div></div><div class="step"><div class="step-num">Step 07</div><div><h3>Affiliate + Partner Commerce</h3><p>Age-targeted recommendations for camps, books, STEM kits, parenting tools, travel, enrichment, and services.</p></div><div class="step-value">High margin</div></div><div class="step"><div class="step-num">Step 08</div><div><h3>Koabi Circle</h3><p>Future invite-only parent network for recommendations, local intelligence, camps, schools, tutors, travel, and enrichment.</p></div><div class="step-value">Membership</div></div></div></div></section>
<section><div class="wrap"><div class="eyebrow">Strategic Positioning</div><h2>Deploying elite growth systems into a fragmented, under-optimized category.</h2><p style="max-width:850px">The parenting and family-activity market is enormous, emotional, evergreen, and fragmented. Most operators are educators, bloggers, Etsy sellers, publishers, or small creators with weak lifecycle systems, weak CRM infrastructure, weak analytics, and generic affiliate programs.</p><div class="three"><div class="card"><h3>Most Competitors</h3><p>Generic landing pages. Generic affiliate links. Minimal lifecycle marketing. Little personalization. Weak segmentation. Limited performance marketing infrastructure.</p></div><div class="card"><h3>Koabi's Approach</h3><p>Elite direct-response systems, AI-assisted personalization, creator-specific funnels, lifecycle automation, affiliate CRM, and segmented product positioning.</p></div><div class="card"><h3>The Opportunity</h3><p>AI lowers content-production cost. Distribution, trust, lifecycle systems, and creator infrastructure become the true moat.</p></div></div><div class="note"><p><strong>Core thesis:</strong> Koabi is not simply a printable activity company. It is an AI-native family entertainment and creator-commerce platform deploying sophisticated systems into a wide-open category.</p></div></div></section>
<section><div class="wrap"><div class="eyebrow">Customer Acquisition</div><h2>Multi-stream acquisition, not single-channel dependency.</h2><p style="max-width:820px">Koabi is designed around a diversified acquisition engine: creator affiliates, bespoke creator landing pages, programmatic SEO, Pinterest, paid media, email lifecycle, referrals, and future membership loops.</p><div class="three"><div class="card"><h3>Creator / Affiliate Engine</h3><p>Mommy bloggers, homeschool creators, family travel creators, Pinterest moms, party bloggers, and low-screen-time advocates promote audience-matched products.</p></div><div class="card"><h3>Audience-Adaptive Landers</h3><p>AI-assisted funnels personalize pages, emails, graphics, copy, and product bundles to each creator’s audience.</p></div><div class="card"><h3>Programmatic SEO</h3><p>Long-tail pages target exact parent intent by age, occasion, theme, holiday, indoor/outdoor use case, travel, and screen-free search terms.</p></div></div><div class="note"><p><strong>Acquisition thesis:</strong> creators drive early trust-based growth; SEO and Pinterest compound; paid media scales only after winning hooks and economics are proven.</p></div></div></section>
<section><div class="wrap"><div class="eyebrow">Product Creation</div><h2>Content production is increasingly industrialized.</h2><div class="grid"><div><p>The category contains enormous volumes of PLR, teacher resources, printable packs, puzzle templates, scavenger structures, worksheet libraries, public-domain inspiration, clipart, Canva kits, and low-performing legacy content.</p><p>The raw mechanics are often commodity. The value is quality control, age calibration, emotional packaging, personalization, design, distribution, and lifecycle monetization.</p></div><div class="card"><p class="quote">“Use PLR and existing mechanics as substrate — not final product.”</p></div></div><div class="three"><div class="card"><h3>Educator-Led Standards</h3><p>Retired teachers and curriculum-minded reviewers define quality standards, age calibration, difficulty, and child engagement thresholds.</p></div><div class="card"><h3>AI-Assisted Transformation</h3><p>AI rewrites, rethemes, modernizes, personalizes, localizes, age-adjusts, and converts raw material into polished variants.</p></div><div class="card"><h3>VA Production Layer</h3><p>Low-cost operators handle formatting, Canva exports, PDF assembly, file naming, Airtable updates, QA checklists, and upload workflows.</p></div></div></div></section>
<section class="dark"><div class="wrap"><div class="eyebrow">Unit Economics</div><h2>The LTV is created downstream.</h2><p style="max-width:780px">A $4.99 product is not attractive by itself. It becomes attractive if it pays for acquisition and feeds a chain of repeat purchases, subscriptions, direct products, and targeted commerce.</p><div class="table"><div class="row"><div class="cell">Initial purchase + bump + upsell</div><div class="cell value">$10–30</div></div><div class="row"><div class="cell">Seasonal repeat purchases</div><div class="cell value">$15–40</div></div><div class="row"><div class="cell">Digital subscription revenue</div><div class="cell value">$20–80+</div></div><div class="row"><div class="cell">Premium physical products</div><div class="cell value">$35+/mo</div></div><div class="row"><div class="cell">Affiliate + partner commerce</div><div class="cell value">$10–40+</div></div><div class="row"><div class="cell">Modelled household LTV</div><div class="cell value">$40–150+</div></div></div></div></section>
<section><div class="wrap"><div class="eyebrow">Brand Architecture</div><h2>Koabi is the platform. ThinkMystery is the first silo.</h2><div class="three"><div class="card"><h3>ThinkMystery</h3><p>Initial wedge: printable mysteries, scavenger hunts, escape rooms, and detective adventures.</p></div><div class="card"><h3>Koabi Play</h3><p>Screen-free games, restaurant kits, travel kits, weekly challenges, and family activity systems.</p></div><div class="card"><h3>Koabi Guides</h3><p>Curated recommendations for camps, books, toys, tools, travel, enrichment, and parenting services.</p></div></div><div class="card" style="margin-top:22px"><h3>Future: Koabi Circle</h3><p>A Hampton-style invite-only parent network: high-trust recommendations, local intelligence, camps, tutors, schools, travel, and intentional parenting systems.</p></div></div></section>
<section class="footer"><div class="wrap"><h2>Koabi is the high-ceiling brand. ThinkMystery is the first wedge.</h2><p>The immediate business is low-friction, searchable, screen-free printable entertainment. The long-term company is a trusted family ecosystem built around intentional childhood, household lifecycle commerce, creator distribution, recurring products, and high-trust parent membership.</p><div style="display:flex;gap:12px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-top:28px"><a class="btn" href="/sales-page-digital/">Digital sales page</a><a class="btn secondary" href="/sales-page-premium/">Premium sales page</a></div></div></section>
</body></html>